	)
	(text_box "steps the battery voltage down to a regulated +3.3V rail. This is the main supply feeding the MCU, display, sensors, and most of the digital side of the phone. The inductor (L1) and caps (C1/C2) around it are standard support parts for a switching regulator - they smooth the output and are sized for the converter's switching frequency."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 232.41 13.97 0)
		(size 55.88 13.97)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0.635)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type color)
			(color 0 255 0 0.2)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(face "Arial")
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 1)
				(bold yes)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "2f882052-9479-42e9-8a9b-5cb3731a1d3e")
	)
	(text_box "the Li-ion charge controller. Manages charging current/termination (set here to ~0.45A charge, 10mA termination via the PROG resistors), does load-sharing so the phone can run on USB while charging, and monitors a thermistor (BAT_THERM) to stop charging if the pack overheats."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 30.48 246.38 0)
		(size 55.88 13.97)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
